[[div class="modal"]]
[[span class="bigtext"]]##42425a|__DESCRIPTION:__## [[/span]] SCP-6651 is believed to be the corpse of an unidentified and unidentifiable creature. Due to its properties, no further information about SCP-6651 can currently be recorded.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]][[span class="bigtext"]]##rgb(66,66,90)|DRAUGR-CLASS##[[/span]] anomalies are considered neutralized or decommissioned but ongoing anomalous phenomena originate from them.[[/span]]

SCP-6651-1 refers to SCP-6651's area of effect, measuring 50 meters in radius around the corpse. Whenever any physical embodiment of a named concept enters SCP-6651-1, it is forced out of the Noosphere,[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]][[span class="bigtext"]]//noosphere// (n).:[[/span]] The area in which the human mind is capable of operating; human thought space.[[/span]] making it incomprehensible to humans.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]][[span class="bigtext"]]##rgb(90,54,83) |ERLOSCHEN-CLASS##[[/span]] anomalies may cause great shifts in reality, however due to altering reality these effects are considered normal.[[/span]]

[[span class="old"]]SCP-6651 refers to a [[span class="fae"]]Fae[[/span]][[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Concept does not seem to correlate to any known ideas within baseline reality; it's currently presumed it refers to some sort of animal species.[[/span]] creature that inhabits a [[span class="fae"]]castle[[/span]][[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Unknown, presumed to be a structure of sorts.[[/span]] in Ogrodzieniec, Poland.[[/span]]

[[/div]]


